metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #473
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

metadata.name: Tomorrow #169
metadata.description:
Tomorrow is probably the biggest uncertainty of our lives.

We hang absolutely everything on tomorrow, the beginning of a new life, training, studies, hopes, expectations, dreams, and many other things, the list can be very long.

But how often do our expectations come true?

This year I hope everyone understood that you cannot hope and count on tomorrow, there is no tomorrow, there is only today.
Stop putting everything off until tomorrow, you may just not notice how your life flew by and you ended up not doing so much.

The shape of the circle was not chosen by chance, it represents the cyclical nature of our lives and everything we do.
But even in this there are exceptions, expecting that tomorrow everything will go on the same scenario, everything goes exactly the opposite.

15 palettes.
5 formats.
2 different drawing modes.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Clerestory #120
metadata.description:
Windows welcome daylight, admit fresh air, and offer a view into the outside world. They rarely shatter, always confess the passage of time, and sometimes allow others a chance to look in.

What would the space you're in feel like if it had no windows?

'Clerestory' is an abstract exploration of stained glass windows, drafting shattered sketches for ten potential locations from various perspectives and moments in time. 

Made with WebGL, p5.js, and <3 | CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: (kinder)Garden, Monuments #172
metadata.description:
When Yazid and Zancan started their fxcollab journey, they knew very little about each other. They learnt about their rich cultural differences, their complementary graphic styles, and a 7-hour timezone difference. What they did have in common was each had two kids about the same age (one a pair of girls, the other boys).

Every kid was born a builder; every kid likes to sit in nature. It’s their way of discovering the world and dreaming of their future accomplishments. While they marvel at the heights of the cities and monuments they construct out of stacks of cubes, parents marvel at their ability to elaborate an unlimited range of worlds out of a limited range of materials. 

This project celebrates the humble and versatile cube. A deceptively simple yet powerful object of play and learning, regardless of age, whether you’re stacking them up in a sandbox, or learning 3D graphics for the first time. 

This project is dedicated to kids, those who were once children, to the dreamers and builders who still enjoy playing with cubes.

Coded in Vanilla JS, the project combines Yazid's iconic “Hashed/Hatched” aesthetic incorporated into childhood wooden toy block structures, and Zancan's signature lush foliage and framework, which enables all iterations to be plottable.
 
Controls (in live view):
- Press [s] to get a SVG file suited for plotters
- Click on the image to download a 4K resolution PNG

metadata.name: Photon resonator n°5 #98
metadata.description:
🜂 ⇶ ⁂ Ω 🜁  ≋ ∂t ↺

Continuously emitting photons
Painting the void with light
Oscillating with the flow

🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱 🝱



-----
* What/How *

1.3 millions particles are continuously emitted by a moving source. A slight asymmetry in the gravitational field allows for continuous expansion.

-----
* Mint preview / Capture *

Minter will get a 4K PNG (2160x2160px bitmap) and a randomly deterministic infinite generative animation.
The 4K capture is made with 6.2 million particles.

-----
* Technics *

This experience is designed to run on a recent GPU (>2016) and displayed on square or rectangle screens from FHD to 8K+ (1920x1080 → 7680x4320) at 60FPS for infinite duration.

- Code written in JavaScript / WebGL / ThreeJS / CuloriJS / GLSL shaders
- Unique random deterministic generative animation (animation is seeded by the fxhash mint hash)
- Infinite animation

-----
* Controls *

Keyboard "Space" : take a PNG capture of the current view (1080x1080 px) — limited to 3 captures by session

-----
@HAL09999 – May 5th, 2023
https://danslesnuages.xyz/about
https://twitter.com/HAL09999

metadata.name: WootScoot Daily Mint-Pass #29
metadata.description:
A Mint-Pass for the WootScoot Daily account.

Gives you access to:
- 24h reserves on all the upcoming dailies
- cheaper prices on all the upcoming dailies
- reserves on WootScoot longform pieces

---

Press space to save the current frame.
Click/Tap the screen to pause/play the animation.
Press -M to toggle mouse follow mode.
Press -T to show/hide the text on the pass

---

Wouter Missler, 2022.

metadata.name: [fxhashturnsone] 2022 A Generative Odyssey #365
metadata.description:
🪐🌌✨

2022 A Generative Odyssey (Story of a traveler)

A simple space landscape generator 🏞
Allows some exploration for curious ones 📡
Don't forget to press "4" to take a panoramic picture 📸🤳

🕳🧭🛰



-----
* Technics *

- JavaScript / ThreeJS / WebGL
- Pure code / no external assets
- Interactive / orbitable
- 8 scenes with unlimited possible variations
- 5 capture / screenshot modes 8K+

-----
* Controls *

Left click / touch + drag : orbit around center of interest
Wheel/pinch : zoom in/out
Keyboard "R" : enable automatic rotation of view

Keyboard "1" : PNG capture the current view at same resolution / ratio 
Keyboard "2" : PNG capture view as square 4320x4320
Keyboard "3" : PNG capture at best resolution 8K (7680x4320)
Keyboard "4" : PNG capture as panoramic view (8192x2304)
Keyboard "5" : PNG capture as super-panoramic (10650x3000)

-----
* URL modifier *

"&r=1"
enables auto rotation of view (equivalent to "R" key press)

-----
* Mint details *

- Mint preview / capture is PNG 1920x1920

-----
@HAL09999 – May/November 2022
